being very manipulative.

00:26:48.550 --> 00:26:51.130 align:middle line:84%
There was a day where she
got out of the hospital,

00:26:51.130 --> 00:26:52.600 align:middle line:90%
and I met her.

00:26:52.600 --> 00:26:57.550 align:middle line:84%
And I gave her money for
travel, and I put her in a cab.

00:26:57.550 --> 00:26:59.560 align:middle line:84%
I took her to lunch,
and she was supposed

00:26:59.560 --> 00:27:04.240 align:middle line:84%
to go to kind of
like a group home.

00:27:04.240 --> 00:27:07.390 align:middle line:90%
And she attempted suicide again.

00:27:07.390 --> 00:27:10.150 align:middle line:90%


00:27:10.150 --> 00:27:13.570 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't be a crutch
for her anymore.

00:27:13.570 --> 00:27:15.790 align:middle line:84%
And for a year, I
didn't speak to her.

00:27:15.790 --> 00:27:19.660 align:middle line:90%


00:27:19.660 --> 00:27:22.090 align:middle line:84%
And that was one of
the hardest things

00:27:22.090 --> 00:27:25.660 align:middle line:90%
I've ever done as a friend.

00:27:25.660 --> 00:27:27.000 align:middle line:90%
I think it broke her heart, too.

00:27:27.000 --> 00:27:30.984 align:middle line:90%


00:27:30.984 --> 00:27:34.785 align:middle line:84%
>> I called her, and I was
experiencing some issues

00:27:34.785 --> 00:27:35.820 align:middle line:90%
and really depressed.

00:27:35.820 --> 00:27:37.195 align:middle line:84%
And I was like,
you know, I don't

00:27:37.195 --> 00:27:39.170 align:middle line:90%
feel like I can live anymore.

00:27:39.170 --> 00:27:42.280 align:middle line:10%
And she told me to
get over myself.

00:27:42.280 --> 00:27:46.040 align:middle line:10%
And I just want to
say, I mean, we've

00:27:46.040 --> 00:27:48.920 align:middle line:10%
reconciled our relationship,
and she's back in my life,

00:27:48.920 --> 00:27:52.400 align:middle line:10%
and we've talked about this
and healed over these things.

00:27:52.400 --> 00:27:57.180 align:middle line:84%
But that is the worst thing
that you could say to someone.

00:27:57.180 --> 00:27:59.010 align:middle line:84%
Another friend of
mine understood

00:27:59.010 --> 00:28:00.245 align:middle line:90%
what I was going through.

00:28:00.245 --> 00:28:02.910 align:middle line:84%
>> I remember actually
talking to her on the phone,

00:28:02.910 --> 00:28:06.570 align:middle line:84%
and talking to her in person,
and smiling a lot with her

00:28:06.570 --> 00:28:09.700 align:middle line:84%
and saying, this
is not a breakdown.

00:28:09.700 --> 00:28:11.190 align:middle line:90%
This is a breakthrough!

00:28:11.190 --> 00:28:13.440 align:middle line:84%
It's kind of like, literally
breaking down a wall

00:28:13.440 --> 00:28:16.050 align:middle line:84%
and going through another
path to be that person you're

00:28:16.050 --> 00:28:20.790 align:middle line:84%
going to be and being willing
to accept that people are going

00:28:20.790 --> 00:28:23.340 align:middle line:84%
to reject you on some level--
your own family, your friends.

00:28:23.340 --> 00:28:26.295 align:middle line:90%


00:28:26.295 --> 00:28:28.200 align:middle line:84%
And again, I
connected with that.

00:28:28.200 --> 00:28:32.610 align:middle line:84%
I myself had attempted suicide
probably four or five times

00:28:32.610 --> 00:28:34.080 align:middle line:90%
in my lifetime.

00:28:34.080 --> 00:28:36.090 align:middle line:84%
And it took me some
time to figure out

00:28:36.090 --> 00:28:39.780 align:middle line:84%
that that feeling
inside was about not

00:28:39.780 --> 00:28:41.945 align:middle line:84%
wanting to be here the
way that I was here,

00:28:41.945 --> 00:28:43.650 align:middle line:90%
not not wanting to be here.

00:28:43.650 --> 00:28:47.610 align:middle line:10%
>> We don't have enough people
