00:29:12.790 --> 00:29:15.520 align:middle line:84%
>> I've been living in
my car for three months--

00:29:15.520 --> 00:29:17.170 align:middle line:90%
or a little over three.

00:29:17.170 --> 00:29:19.360 align:middle line:84%
I have incredible
people in my life.

00:29:19.360 --> 00:29:22.090 align:middle line:84%
And right as I lost my family,
I found a brand new one

00:29:22.090 --> 00:29:23.960 align:middle line:90%
that is incredible.

00:29:23.960 --> 00:29:27.190 align:middle line:84%
This place, SoulFood
family, they are amazing.

00:29:27.190 --> 00:29:31.580 align:middle line:84%
It is just a beautiful community
of open-minded, loving people.

00:29:31.580 --> 00:29:36.260 align:middle line:84%
>> I think a lot of people
would say that Adam was broken,

00:29:36.260 --> 00:29:37.790 align:middle line:90%
and I don't view it that way.

00:29:37.790 --> 00:29:40.486 align:middle line:84%
I think our culture
