very unusual beliefs,

00:31:46.480 --> 00:31:48.680 align:middle line:84%
there's meaning to
those experiences.

00:31:48.680 --> 00:31:53.510 align:middle line:84%
Only in the Western world have
developed this bizarre idea

00:31:53.510 --> 00:31:56.240 align:middle line:84%
that hearing voices and
having strange ideas

00:31:56.240 --> 00:31:59.450 align:middle line:90%
has no meaning at all.

00:31:59.450 --> 00:32:02.390 align:middle line:84%
It's just a symptom of
these imagined illnesses

00:32:02.390 --> 00:32:05.065 align:middle line:84%
that biological psychiatry
is actually created.

00:32:05.065 --> 00:32:17.436 align:middle line:90%


00:32:17.436 --> 00:32:20.760 align:middle line:84%
>> While mentoring young
photographers on the Navajo

00:32:20.760 --> 00:32:23.910 align:middle line:84%
nation, I met Morgan
[? Yazzie ? ].

00:32:23.910 --> 00:32:26.130 align:middle line:10%
He said he had been
having dizzy spells

00:32:26.130 --> 00:32:30.840 align:middle line:10%
and hallucinations in his
20s but tried to ignore them.

00:32:30.840 --> 00:32:34.410 align:middle line:84%
They started to happen more
frequently until he finally

00:32:34.410 --> 00:32:37.440 align:middle line:90%
had what he called a stroke.

00:32:37.440 --> 00:32:40.530 align:middle line:84%
His friend, Sam
[INAUDIBLE],, a medicine man,

00:32:40.530 --> 00:32:44.460 align:middle line:84%
did a ceremony for him and
told Morgan he was ignoring

00:32:44.460 --> 00:32:45.780 align:middle line:90%
a calling--

00:32:45.780 --> 00:32:49.080 align:middle line:90%
a calling to be a medicine man.

00:32:49.080 --> 00:32:51.600 align:middle line:84%
And I've heard this
several times before.

00:32:51.600 --> 00:32:53.700 align:middle line:84%
If you ignore the
calling, there's

00:32:53.700 --> 00:32:58.170 align:middle line:84%
a good chance that you could
get sick and possibly die.

00:32:58.170 --> 00:33:01.650 align:middle line:84%
Many say it's a transformation
waiting to happen

00:33:01.650 --> 00:33:03.130 align:middle line:90%
that has to be dealt with.

00:33:03.130 --> 00:33:10.585 align:middle line:90%


00:33:10.585 --> 00:33:13.510 align:middle line:84%
>> I couldn't go into
the bathroom to shower

00:33:13.510 --> 00:33:16.360 align:middle line:84%
because people
were smoking crack.

00:33:16.360 --> 00:33:19.160 align:middle line:84%
I felt like I was about
to harm myself again,

00:33:19.160 --> 00:33:20.280 align:middle line:90%
and I didn't want that.

00:33:20.280 --> 00:33:23.590 align:middle line:84%
And so I called the nurse's
station, and one of the nurses

00:33:23.590 --> 00:33:24.820 align:middle line:90%
said, come back.

00:33:24.820 --> 00:33:28.390 align:middle line:10%
Come back and we'll help you.

00:33:28.390 --> 00:33:30.070 align:middle line:84%
I had an intake with
the psychiatrist

00:33:30.070 --> 00:33:31.370 align:middle line:90%
at the emergency room.

00:33:31.370 --> 00:33:34.771 align:middle line:84%
And after him questioning
me, and seeing my records,

00:33:34.771 --> 00:33:36.520 align:middle line:84%
and seeing that I had
been in the hospital

00:33:36.520 --> 00:33:40.450 align:middle line:84%
for already six weeks,
he didn't believe me.

00:33:40.450 --> 00:33:42.300 align:middle line:84%
He said, I'm going
to send you home--

00:33:42.300 --> 00:33:44.900 align:middle line:90%
that you don't need to be here.

00:33:44.900 --> 00:33:47.410 align:middle line:84%
I walked out of the
emergency room door.

00:33:47.410 --> 00:33:52.960 align:middle line:84%
I had just filled a prescription
bottle of antipsychotic pills.

00:33:52.960 --> 00:33:55.750 align:middle line:84%
And right outside
of the hospital,

00:33:55.750 --> 00:34:00.380 align:middle line:84%
I took all the
pills in the bottle.

00:34:00.380 --> 00:34:03.470 align:middle line:84%
When I woke up, I was
strapped to a bed.

00:34:03.470 --> 00:34:09.665 align:middle line:84%
When I opened my eyes, I was
just like, how am I here?

00:34:09.665 --> 00:34:11.816 align:middle line:84%
[STIFLING TEARS]
Why am I still here?

00:34:11.816 --> 00:34:17.454 align:middle line:90%


00:34:17.454 --> 00:34:18.370 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't believe it.

00:34:18.370 --> 00:34:25.560 align:middle line:90%


00:34:25.560 --> 00:34:29.219 align:middle line:10%
But I am very, very
grateful for that moment,

00:34:29.219 --> 00:34:33.389 align:middle line:10%
because that's the
moment I knew that there

00:34:33.389 --> 00:34:34.879 align:middle line:10%
was a purpose for my life.

00:34:34.879 --> 00:34:35.679 align:middle line:90%
There was a reason.

00:34:35.679 --> 00:34:38.670 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know it,
but I knew that there

00:34:38.670 --> 00:34:43.493 align:middle line:84%
