00:58:24.710 --> 00:58:27.780 align:middle line:84%
At 70, she had an active
healing practice--

00:58:27.780 --> 00:58:31.200 align:middle line:84%
working day and night, seeing
people one after another

00:58:31.200 --> 00:58:33.030 align:middle line:84%
during the time I
stayed with her.

00:58:33.030 --> 00:58:35.580 align:middle line:90%
[TRIBAL DRUMS]

00:58:35.580 --> 00:58:37.830 align:middle line:84%
One night, while
going into a trance

00:58:37.830 --> 00:58:41.370 align:middle line:84%
to help a woman who was having
trouble in her pregnancy,

00:58:41.370 --> 00:58:44.800 align:middle line:90%
she collapsed.

00:58:44.800 --> 00:58:48.690 align:middle line:90%
Then she got up and kept going.

00:58:48.690 --> 00:58:53.310 align:middle line:84%
When she was about 12 or 13, she
started having intense dreams,

00:58:53.310 --> 00:58:57.900 align:middle line:84%
hearing voices, and feeling
confused and frightened.

00:58:57.900 --> 00:58:59.850 align:middle line:84%
She would often
go into the forest

00:58:59.850 --> 00:59:02.160 align:middle line:90%
alone and be gone for days.

00:59:02.160 --> 00:59:04.650 align:middle line:84%
And her parents were
extremely worried.

00:59:04.650 --> 00:59:07.200 align:middle line:84%
Her grandfather,
who was a shaman,

00:59:07.200 --> 00:59:13.230 align:middle line:84%
recognized these traits in
her and began mentoring her.

00:59:13.230 --> 00:59:16.170 align:middle line:84%
While making [INAUDIBLE]
portrait the next morning

00:59:16.170 --> 00:59:18.660 align:middle line:84%
and looking into
her face, I thought

00:59:18.660 --> 00:59:22.740 align:middle line:84%
of her devotion to her patients
and how much time and energy

00:59:22.740 --> 00:59:25.390 align:middle line:90%
she gave as a healer.

00:59:25.390 --> 00:59:28.140 align:middle line:84%
I was reminded how
important our relationships

00:59:28.140 --> 00:59:31.998 align:middle line:90%
are to the healing process.

00:59:31.998 --> 00:59:36.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Peers are taught to meet
other peers where they're at.

00:59:36.710 --> 00:59:40.950 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of time in other
medical or clinical settings,

00:59:40.950 --> 00:59:43.070 align:middle line:90%
you have this hierarchy.

00:59:43.070 --> 00:59:46.530 align:middle line:84%
But in peer work, it's almost
like talking to a friend.

00:59:46.530 --> 00:59:48.660 align:middle line:84%
It's like saying, I've
been through this.

00:59:48.660 --> 00:59:49.920 align:middle line:90%
What have you been through?

00:59:49.920 --> 00:59:52.260 align:middle line:90%
Share your story with me.

00:59:52.260 --> 00:59:55.080 align:middle line:84%
I really, truly
value my life now,

00:59:55.080 --> 01:00:00.280 align:middle line:84%
and I have a focus and awareness
that I didn't have before.

01:00:00.280 --> 01:00:04.430 align:middle line:84%
>> What we're seeing happen in
the US and internationally is

01:00:04.430 --> 01:00:09.200 align:middle line:84%
a grassroots democratization
of mental health.

01:00:09.200 --> 01:00:12.500 align:middle line:84%
We have lost touch
in our medical system

01:00:12.500 --> 01:00:15.500 align:middle line:84%
from some of the simple
needs that people

01:00:15.500 --> 01:00:17.960 align:middle line:84%
have for connection-- the
simple needs that people

01:00:17.960 --> 01:00:19.700 align:middle line:90%
have for community.

01:00:19.700 --> 01:00:22.486 align:middle line:84%
And because the mental health
system isn't providing it,

01:00:22.486 --> 01:00:24.360 align:middle line:84%
people who've been in
the system are starting

01:00:24.360 --> 01:00:26.742 align:middle line:90%
to provide it for ourselves.

01:00:26.742 --> 01:00:32.990 align:middle line:84%
>> Today's session is about
finding strength after trauma.

01:00:32.990 --> 01:00:35.120 align:middle line:84%
As a survivor of
childhood trauma,

01:00:35.120 --> 01:00:38.570 align:middle line:84%
as someone who was sexually
abused by a family member,

01:00:38.570 --> 01:00:43.190 align:middle line:84%
I can say that I'm a
survivor of trauma,

01:00:43.190 --> 01:00:46.348 align:middle line:90%
and I know that I'm not alone.

01:00:46.348 --> 01:00:49.970 align:middle line:84%
>> It's very, very important
that we have storytelling from

01:00:49.970 --> 01:00:53.120 align:middle line:84%
people who've lived through
psychosis and who've discovered

01:00:53.120 --> 01:00:56.600 align:middle line:84%
alternatives to medications
and alternatives to diagnosis

01:00:56.600 --> 01:00:58.490 align:middle line:84%
because that's
really the expertise.

01:00:58.490 --> 01:01:00.140 align:middle line:90%
>> Your story is important.

01:01:00.140 --> 01:01:01.025 align:middle line:90%
You are unique.

01:01:01.025 --> 01:01:04.000 align:middle line:90%


01:01:04.000 --> 01:01:06.470 align:middle line:84%
Own your title--
trauma survivor.

01:01:06.470 --> 01:01:08.774 align:middle line:90%
Find your strength.

01:01:08.774 --> 01:01:12.678 align:middle line:90%
>> Come on, [INAUDIBLE]

01:01:12.678 --> 01:01:15.606 align:middle line:90%


01:01:15.606 --> 01:01:20.730 align:middle line:84%
>> My mother-- now
she's facing death.

01:01:20.730 --> 01:01:25.340 align:middle line:84%
Me sharing my spiritual
side with her--

01:01:25.340 --> 01:01:28.550 align:middle line:90%
she was open to it.

01:01:28.550 --> 01:01:29.550 align:middle line:90%
And it was amazing.

01:01:29.550 --> 01:01:32.290 align:middle line:90%
And she really did listen to me.

01:01:32.290 --> 01:01:35.980 align:middle line:84%
And it was one of the
first times in so long

01:01:35.980 --> 01:01:39.090 align:middle line:84%
that I had been able to
share my heart with someone

01:01:39.090 --> 01:01:40.034 align:middle line:90%
in my family.

01:01:40.034 --> 01:01:45.710 align:middle line:90%


01:01:45.710 --> 01:01:49.610 align:middle line:84%
It's been really
intense on the family.

01:01:49.610 --> 01:01:51.620 align:middle line:90%
It's been really intense on me.

01:01:51.620 --> 01:01:55.430 align:middle line:84%
I see the death of my
mother being a catalyst

01:01:55.430 --> 01:01:59.600 align:middle line:84%
to bring a whole lot of
necessary love and appreciation

01:01:59.600 --> 01:02:01.802 align:middle line:90%
into my family.

01:02:01.802 --> 01:02:03.778 align:middle line:90%
And that was what she was about.

01:02:03.778 --> 01:02:09.710 align:middle line:90%


01:02:09.710 --> 01:02:13.960 align:middle line:84%
The first time I was diagnosed
insane I had something to say.

01:02:13.960 --> 01:02:16.200 align:middle line:84%
And I've looked back at the
things that I had to say,

01:02:16.200 --> 01:02:18.740 align:middle line:84%
and I don't think
any of it's insane.

01:02:18.740 --> 01:02:21.160 align:middle line:84%
It's a very damaging
thing to not

01:02:21.160 --> 01:02:23.380 align:middle line:84%
be able to trust
your own perspective.

01:02:23.380 --> 01:02:28.366 align:middle line:84%
When you can't do that,
that really fucks you up.

01:02:28.366 --> 01:02:33.790 align:middle line:84%
>> What we do in the West
is to constrain individuals.

01:02:33.790 --> 01:02:36.190 align:middle line:84%
People start to
manage your experience

01:02:36.190 --> 01:02:40.360 align:middle line:84%
at a level which takes
your agency away, robs you

01:02:40.360 --> 01:02:44.375 align:middle line:84%
of your autonomy, makes you
feel like they don't trust you.

01:02:44.375 --> 01:02:45.685 align:middle line:90%
That's not what you want to do.

01:02:45.685 --> 01:02:49.090 align:middle line:84%
>> Once I internalized a
mentally ill identity--

01:02:49.090 --> 01:02:53.350 align:middle line:84%
once I came to see myself as
having this disease living

01:02:53.350 --> 01:02:56.740 align:middle line:84%
inside of me, I stopped
trusting in my intuition,

01:02:56.740 --> 01:02:58.450 align:middle line:90%
because it was sick.

01:02:58.450 --> 01:03:02.460 align:middle line:90%


01:03:02.460 --> 01:03:05.970 align:middle line:84%
The only way to
find myself again

01:03:05.970 --> 01:03:09.600 align:middle line:84%
and to get back to an authentic
sense of self is to feel this,

01:03:09.600 --> 01:03:11.670 align:middle line:84%
and to listen to it,
and to explore it,

01:03:11.670 --> 01:03:13.499 align:middle line:90%
and to not be afraid of it.

01:03:13.499 --> 01:03:14.790 align:middle line:90%
So that's what I started to do.

01:03:14.790 --> 01:03:24.410 align:middle line:90%


01:03:24.410 --> 01:03:28.480 align:middle line:10%
>> I traveled to the Amur
River in Eastern Siberia,

01:03:28.480 --> 01:03:30.440 align:middle line:10%
where the word
shaman originated.

01:03:30.440 --> 01:03:33.340 align:middle line:90%


01:03:33.340 --> 01:03:36.280 align:middle line:84%
There, I met [INAUDIBLE],,
a very respected healer

01:03:36.280 --> 01:03:37.640 align:middle line:90%
for over 60 years.

01:03:37.640 --> 01:03:40.240 align:middle line:90%


01:03:40.240 --> 01:03:43.840 align:middle line:84%
She was forced to practice
in secret for decades

01:03:43.840 --> 01:03:47.830 align:middle line:84%
until the Soviet Union
collapsed in 1989

01:03:47.830 --> 01:03:50.410 align:middle line:84%
and was just one of
two remaining shaman

01:03:50.410 --> 01:03:53.770 align:middle line:90%
in her [INAUDIBLE] culture.

01:03:53.770 --> 01:03:55.810 align:middle line:84%
Nine-year-old
Sasha-- [INAUDIBLE]

01:03:55.810 --> 01:03:57.850 align:middle line:90%
neighbor in their village.

01:03:57.850 --> 01:04:01.030 align:middle line:84%
Her grandmother told us that
Sasha has fainting spells

01:04:01.030 --> 01:04:03.760 align:middle line:84%
and hears voices,
both considered

01:04:03.760 --> 01:04:07.630 align:middle line:90%
signs of shamanic potential.

01:04:07.630 --> 01:04:11.200 align:middle line:10%
Unfortunately, just three
weeks after my visit,

01:04:11.200 --> 01:04:16.090 align:middle line:10%
[INAUDIBLE] passed away,
leaving Sasha without a mentor.

01:04:16.090 --> 01:04:18.280 align:middle line:10%
At the time, it seemed
I was witnessing

01:04:18.280 --> 01:04:20.770 align:middle line:10%
the disappearance of
an age-old tradition

01:04:20.770 --> 01:04:23.470 align:middle line:10%
in this corner of Siberia.

01:04:23.470 --> 01:04:26.290 align:middle line:84%
However, as I later
discovered, shamanism

01:04:26.290 --> 01:04:31.040 align:middle line:84%
is re-emerging in very
unexpected places.

01:04:31.040 --> 01:04:34.960 align:middle line:84%
Ekhaya met a South African
shaman, known as a sangoma,

01:04:34.960 --> 01:04:38.060 align:middle line:84%
living in Baltimore and
began working with her.

01:04:38.060 --> 01:04:42.790 align:middle line:84%
>> She told me that I was
called to be a healer, a shaman.

01:04:42.790 --> 01:04:47.410 align:middle line:84%
And I had been feeling
that inside of me.

01:04:47.410 --> 01:04:49.720 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of times,
we need confirmation.

01:04:49.720 --> 01:04:52.150 align:middle line:84%
And so that was my
absolute-- as soon as she

01:04:52.150 --> 01:04:54.040 align:middle line:90%
said that, I was in tears.

01:04:54.040 --> 01:04:57.220 align:middle line:84%
Her exact words were, you
should be doing what I'm doing.

01:04:57.220 --> 01:04:59.032 align:middle line:84%
You have priesthood
responsibilities.

01:04:59.032 --> 01:05:00.490 align:middle line:84%
You should be doing
what I'm doing.

01:05:00.490 --> 01:05:03.250 align:middle line:90%


01:05:03.250 --> 01:05:06.040 align:middle line:84%
I get on a packed
bus for a four-hour

01:05:06.040 --> 01:05:09.790 align:middle line:84%
trip to Baltimore, Maryland,
where my baba is, my teacher.

01:05:09.790 --> 01:05:14.500 align:middle line:84%
And during that time, I'm
just really meditating

01:05:14.500 --> 01:05:17.710 align:middle line:84%
and just preparing
myself for everything,

01:05:17.710 --> 01:05:20.290 align:middle line:84%
because it is a lot
of intense work--

01:05:20.290 --> 01:05:22.603 align:middle line:84%
beautiful work but
very intense work.

01:05:22.603 --> 01:05:26.950 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

01:05:26.950 --> 01:05:32.280 align:middle line:90%


01:05:32.280 --> 01:05:37.590 align:middle line:84%
The sangoma training involves
humbling yourself completely

01:05:37.590 --> 01:05:40.515 align:middle line:84%
to your teacher and
to your ancestors.

01:05:40.515 --> 01:05:44.880 align:middle line:84%
>> What you have to do as
a twaza is submit yourself,

01:05:44.880 --> 01:05:47.790 align:middle line:90%
your ego, all of your beliefs.

01:05:47.790 --> 01:05:49.470 align:middle line:90%
You have to sit on the floor.

01:05:49.470 --> 01:05:51.210 align:middle line:90%
You have to eat with your hands.

01:05:51.210 --> 01:05:53.806 align:middle line:84%
You have to surrender
to your ancestors.

01:05:53.806 --> 01:06:00.030 align:middle line:84%
>> A twaza is an initiate to
become a traditional South

01:06:00.030 --> 01:06:01.260 align:middle line:90%
African healer.

01:06:01.260 --> 01:06:04.190 align:middle line:84%
>> During slavery, we
lost a lot of who we were.

01:06:04.190 --> 01:06:05.880 align:middle line:84%
But what you can't
take from a person

01:06:05.880 --> 01:06:07.420 align:middle line:90%
is what's in their blood.

01:06:07.420 --> 01:06:11.070 align:middle line:84%
So if it's in your blood,
it's going to be in you.

01:06:11.070 --> 01:06:12.990 align:middle line:84%
The only way that she
received the calling

01:06:12.990 --> 01:06:17.070 align:middle line:84%
is because someone in her family
was a traditional South African

01:06:17.070 --> 01:06:18.220 align:middle line:90%
healer.

01:06:18.220 --> 01:06:21.190 align:middle line:84%
Her ancestors that are in her
blood-- that they're saying,

01:06:21.190 --> 01:06:21.990 align:middle line:90%
wake up.

01:06:21.990 --> 01:06:22.830 align:middle line:90%
Wake up.

01:06:22.830 --> 01:06:27.990 align:middle line:84%
They're waking her up to them
to say, you are our child,

01:06:27.990 --> 01:06:30.025 align:middle line:84%
and this is how we
want you to live.

01:06:30.025 --> 01:06:32.340 align:middle line:84%
>> At the start
of my initiation,

01:06:32.340 --> 01:06:36.960 align:middle line:84%
I experienced all of the
problems that I was having,

01:06:36.960 --> 01:06:40.410 align:middle line:84%
all of the anxieties
and depression,

01:06:40.410 --> 01:06:43.500 align:middle line:90%
and I was being pushed.

01:06:43.500 --> 01:06:48.930 align:middle line:84%
And I hurt, and I cried,
and my body ached.

01:06:48.930 --> 01:06:51.720 align:middle line:90%
The medications drown you out.

01:06:51.720 --> 01:06:53.220 align:middle line:90%
They mask you.

01:06:53.220 --> 01:06:55.830 align:middle line:84%
They put a fog
over your problems,

01:06:55.830 --> 01:06:57.870 align:middle line:84%
and you really are in
touch with yourself.

01:06:57.870 --> 01:06:59.140 align:middle line:90%
You don't feel things.

01:06:59.140 --> 01:07:02.790 align:middle line:84%
I've had to face all my
fears, all the things that

01:07:02.790 --> 01:07:06.480 align:middle line:84%
made me upset and angry, all
the people that I've hurt.

01:07:06.480 --> 01:07:10.170 align:middle line:84%
I've had to face
it and be with it

01:07:10.170 --> 01:07:13.474 align:middle line:84%
before I was able to
release it and let it go.

01:07:13.474 --> 01:07:20.166 align:middle line:90%


01:07:20.166 --> 01:07:24.160 align:middle line:84%
>> Adam started turning a corner
and moved into an apartment

01:07:24.160 --> 01:07:25.480 align:middle line:90%
with a friend.

01:07:25.480 --> 01:07:27.670 align:middle line:84%
It had been three
long years since he

01:07:27.670 --> 01:07:30.070 align:middle line:84%
was turned away from
the meditation center

01:07:30.070 --> 01:07:31.900 align:middle line:90%
and alienated from his family.

01:07:31.900 --> 01:07:35.650 align:middle line:84%
>> I had an opportunity for
about a year to be an autistic

01:07:35.650 --> 01:07:40.390 align:middle line:84%
counselor, and that was
really powerful for me.

01:07:40.390 --> 01:07:43.690 align:middle line:84%
I know music therapy
is a practice

01:07:43.690 --> 01:07:46.260 align:middle line:84%
that more and more
people are looking into.

01:07:46.260 --> 01:07:47.060 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

01:07:47.060 --> 01:07:48.580 align:middle line:84%
>> Maybe I should be
one of those people.

01:07:48.580 --> 01:07:49.546 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah!

01:07:49.546 --> 01:07:55.825 align:middle line:90%


01:07:55.825 --> 01:08:01.540 align:middle line:84%
>> My mind was just interpreting
everything as hate and rape,

01:08:01.540 --> 01:08:04.930 align:middle line:84%
and that's all it
knew at that point.

01:08:04.930 --> 01:08:09.100 align:middle line:84%
And that's what became this
evil personality in my head

01:08:09.100 --> 01:08:14.340 align:middle line:90%
that has gotten a lot better.

01:08:14.340 --> 01:08:17.340 align:middle line:84%
Actually, my dad just called
me before this interview

01:08:17.340 --> 01:08:21.270 align:middle line:84%
and was saying he originally
just wanted to be by himself.

01:08:21.270 --> 01:08:23.310 align:middle line:84%
And now, he wants
to come hang out.

01:08:23.310 --> 01:08:24.790 align:middle line:90%
I think he's coming over here.

01:08:24.790 --> 01:08:27.810 align:middle line:90%
We're going to have beers.

01:08:27.810 --> 01:08:29.880 align:middle line:90%
Merry Christmas.

01:08:29.880 --> 01:08:32.040 align:middle line:90%
That makes me so happy.

01:08:32.040 --> 01:08:33.270 align:middle line:90%
That's magic.

01:08:33.270 --> 01:08:35.310 align:middle line:84%
Now, he's coming
over to my place.

01:08:35.310 --> 01:08:39.420 align:middle line:84%
I have a place for my
dad to come over to.

01:08:39.420 --> 01:08:40.470 align:middle line:90%
And he's down.

01:08:40.470 --> 01:08:42.011 align:middle line:84%
And he's actually
down to talk to me.

01:08:42.011 --> 01:08:45.253 align:middle line:90%


01:08:45.253 --> 01:08:46.449 align:middle line:90%
>> That's great.

01:08:46.449 --> 01:08:47.249 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

01:08:47.249 --> 01:08:50.742 align:middle line:90%
[SPIRITUAL SINGING]

01:08:50.742 --> 01:08:58.948 align:middle line:90%


01:08:58.948 --> 01:09:01.920 align:middle line:84%
>> Ekhaya has come
a very long way.

01:09:01.920 --> 01:09:05.370 align:middle line:84%
When she first came to me,
she was very unstable, all

01:09:05.370 --> 01:09:07.590 align:middle line:84%
over the place, not
sure of herself,

01:09:07.590 --> 01:09:12.210 align:middle line:84%
confused, and just not
clear about who she was.

01:09:12.210 --> 01:09:14.735 align:middle line:90%


01:09:14.735 --> 01:09:19.710 align:middle line:84%
>> But like, OK, finally, I
know why I'm on this Earth.

01:09:19.710 --> 01:09:23.880 align:middle line:84%
I know why I'm so sensitive to
all these things and energies.

01:09:23.880 --> 01:09:25.890 align:middle line:84%
I understand why I
have visions now.

01:09:25.890 --> 01:09:26.819 align:middle line:90%
I understand.

01:09:26.819 --> 01:09:28.859 align:middle line:90%
And I had to go find it.

01:09:28.859 --> 01:09:30.990 align:middle line:84%
You tell your therapist
or your psychiatrist,

01:09:30.990 --> 01:09:32.130 align:middle line:90%
and they say you're ill.

01:09:32.130 --> 01:09:35.670 align:middle line:84%
They say you have borderline
personality disorder.

01:09:35.670 --> 01:09:37.950 align:middle line:90%
You have chronic depression.

01:09:37.950 --> 01:09:40.560 align:middle line:84%
And these are the drugs
that you need to take.

01:09:40.560 --> 01:09:42.000 align:middle line:84%
This is what's
going to help you.

01:09:42.000 --> 01:09:45.120 align:middle line:84%
But nobody told me, this
is a spiritual matter,

01:09:45.120 --> 01:09:47.670 align:middle line:90%
and you are gifted.

01:09:47.670 --> 01:09:52.093 align:middle line:84%
And now it's time for
you to hone these gifts.

01:09:52.093 --> 01:09:55.570 align:middle line:84%
(EMOTIONAL) And it
was just so amazing.

01:09:55.570 --> 01:10:00.270 align:middle line:84%
I'm so grateful, because
it has changed my life.

01:10:00.270 --> 01:10:05.250 align:middle line:84%
I know who I am
without a doubt, 100%.

01:10:05.250 --> 01:10:08.670 align:middle line:84%
I know who I am, and it
